[src:self-supervised-learning/unsupervised-learning] An Autoencoder is a 3-layer CAM network, where the middle layer is supposed to be some internal representation of input patterns.
[src:self-supervised-learning/unsupervised-learning] The weights are named phi & theta rather than W and V as in Helmholtz—a cosmetic difference.
